6 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2667 of Title 63, unless there
8 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 As used in this act:
10 1. "Commissioner" means the Oklahoma Commissioner of Health;
11 2. "Department" means the State Department of Health;
12 3. "Emergency care" means health care services provided to
13 achieve stabilization as needed for conditions that reasonably
14 appear to constitute a life- or limb-threatening emergency based on
15 the presenting symptoms of the patient;
16 4. "Facility" means a short-term emergency and nonemergency
17 hybrid medical facility;
18 5. "Maximum emergency stay period" means any patient who is
19 treated for an emergency situation and is prohibited from being
20 treated or held any longer than twenty-four (24) hours so long as
21 the necessary treatment required is deemed an emergency. Maximum
22 emergency stay period shall not apply to patients that are
23 stabilized and needing further treatment from being provided
24 nonemergency care;
Req. No. 13125 Page 2

1 6. "Nonemergency care" means all health care that is not for
2 life-threatening conditions or covered as emergency care under an
3 existing health care policy, including, but not limited to, the
4 following services:
5 a. diagnostic testing,
6 b. lab testing,
7 c. outpatient services,
8 d. primary care, and
9 e. X-rays, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), and other
10 types of imaging; and
11 7. "Short-term emergency and nonemergency hybrid medical
12 facility" means a dual-sided facility, structurally separate and
13 distinct from a hospital that is open twenty-four (24) hours per day
14 and seven (7) days a week, with one side of the facility providing
15 emergency care and the other side of the facility providing
16 nonemergency care.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2668 of Title 63, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Except as provided by Section 3 of this act, a person shall
21 not establish or operate a short-term emergency and nonemergency
22 hybrid medical facility in this state without a license issued under
23 this act.
